@j95lee I think you're missing the forest for the trees here. Red Sonja is a low budget sword & sorcery movie. The status quo of this sort of movie since the 70s has been bottom of the barrel slop, so the quality of this new RS shouldn't serve as an indictment of modern Hollywood filmmaking, but rather the genre it represents. And if we're talking mainstream, we can't exclude the films of Christopher Nolan, Denis Villeneuve, David Fincher, or Steven Soderberg, who I think are all brilliant directors, each of whom have movies I'd put in my top 25. 

While just outside of mainstream, we have directors like Alex Garland, Ari Aster, and Robert Eggers making some of the coolest shit on the silver screen in my eyes.

So yeah, if you only watch the Spandex/dinosaur/robot movies, you're really doing yourself a disservice.
